HEADWORD: Paytine
<hw>Pay"tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
alkaloid obtained from a white bark resembling that of the cinchona,
first brought from <etsep>Payta</etsep>, in
<country>Peru</country>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

